OL,3,CTributes to 'legendary' defence
OL,4,Cbarrister Courtenay Griffiths KC
OL,6,F"Like all great barristers, he treated
OL,7,Fthe courtroom as though he was the
OL,8,Fleading man in his own drama.
OL,10,F"His exchanges were often devastating
OL,11,Ffor witnesses, but those of us on the
OL,12,Fpress benches were delighted.
OL,14,F"He never failed to deliver the quotes
OL,15,Fwe needed for our copy.
OL,17,F"Courtenay was charm itself. Serious
OL,18,Fabout his work but never too serious
OL,19,Fto be friendly and always with a
OL,20,Ftwinkle in his eye. RIP"
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUvD@AOUyD@AOU|D@XO]
